unittitle_ssm: Kentucky Miners Defense Records
abstract_ssm: The Kentucky Miners Defense was formed to help free miners and local mine union officials convicted of conspiracy to murder three sheriff's deputies in Evarts, Harlan County, Kentucky during the miners' strike of May 1931. The committee was headed by Herbert Mahler, a former official of the Industrial Workers of the World. The collection contains court transcripts, statements and other documents relating to the miners' cases, as well as news releases, United States Senate subcommittee hearing reports, and excerpts from the Daily Worker.
